extremeMlagPeerTable.name: extremeMlagPeerTable
extremeMlagPeerTable.description: This table contains MLAG peer entries. This table contains a MLAG peer switch association structure, associates an MLAG peer structure with an MLAG peer switch IP address. Displays User configured items, MLAG peer switch state, MLAG port count and health-check statistics.

extremeMlagPeerEntry.name: extremeMlagPeerEntry
extremeMlagPeerEntry.description: An entry in the MLAG Peer Table

extremeMlagPeerName.name: extremeMlagPeerName
extremeMlagPeerName.description: The name of the MLAG Peer switch. MLAG Peer names must be alpha-numeric and must start with an alpha character.

extremeMlagPeerVlan.name: extremeMlagPeerVlan
extremeMlagPeerVlan.description: The name of the VLAN through which the MLAG Peer can be reached.

extremeMlagPeerVR.name: extremeMlagPeerVR
extremeMlagPeerVR.description: The name of the VR with which the MLAG peer VLAN is associated with.

extremeMlagLocalAddrType.name: extremeMlagLocalAddrType
extremeMlagLocalAddrType.description: The IP address type of the extremeMlagLocalIP object.

extremeMlagLocalIP.name: extremeMlagLocalIP
extremeMlagLocalIP.description: Local Switch IPAddress of ISC connection.

extremeMlagPeerAddrType.name: extremeMlagPeerAddrType
extremeMlagPeerAddrType.description: The IP address type of the extremeMlagPeerIP object.

extremeMlagPeerIP.name: extremeMlagPeerIP
extremeMlagPeerIP.description: MLAG peer IP address for the ISC. The specified IP address must be contained within an existing direct route.

extremeMlagPeerPortCount.name: extremeMlagPeerPortCount
extremeMlagPeerPortCount.description: Number of MLAG Ports associated with this MLAG peer

extremeMlagPeerCheckPointStatus.name: extremeMlagPeerCheckPointStatus
extremeMlagPeerCheckPointStatus.description: Checkpointing Status of this MLAG peer

extremeMlagPeerRxHellos.name: extremeMlagPeerRxHellos
extremeMlagPeerRxHellos.description: Number of Hellos received from the peer

extremeMlagPeerRxCheckpointMsgs.name: extremeMlagPeerRxCheckpointMsgs
extremeMlagPeerRxCheckpointMsgs.description: Number of Checkpoint Messages received from the peer

extremeMlagPeerUptime.name: extremeMlagPeerUptime
extremeMlagPeerUptime.description: Specifies the time that the Connectivity with the peer is up

extremeMlagPeerLocalTxInterval.name: extremeMlagPeerLocalTxInterval
extremeMlagPeerLocalTxInterval.description: Length of the time in milli seconds between health check hello packets transmitted by this switch.

extremeMlagPeerRemoteTxInterval.name: extremeMlagPeerRemoteTxInterval
extremeMlagPeerRemoteTxInterval.description: Transmitting Hello Interval of Peer Switch in milli seconds

extremeMlagPeerTxHellos.name: extremeMlagPeerTxHellos
extremeMlagPeerTxHellos.description: Number of Health Check Hellos transmitted

extremeMlagPeerCfgLacpMac.name: extremeMlagPeerCfgLacpMac
extremeMlagPeerCfgLacpMac.description: This MAC address specifies the MLAG LACP MAC configured on this switch. If configured, this MAC is used as the System Identifier in the LACPDUs sent over the MLAG Ports. If not configured, the MAC address of MLAG peer having highest IP address for ISC control VLAN is chosen as the System Identifier in the LACPDUs sent over the MALG ports.

extremeMlagPeerOperLacpMac.name: extremeMlagPeerOperLacpMac
extremeMlagPeerOperLacpMac.description: This MAC address specifies the MLAG LACP MAC that is being used as the System Identifier in the LACPDUs sent over the MLAG Ports. This may be different from extremeMlagPeerCfgLacpMac if same extremeMlagPeerCfgLacpMac is not configured on both the MLAG peers.

extremeMlagPortTable.name: extremeMlagPortTable
extremeMlagPortTable.description: This table contains Mlag port entries. Binds a local port or LAG port to an MLAG port uniquely indentified by the MLAG Id value. Once the MLAG group binding is made, any change to load sharing on MLAG ports is disallowed. Displays User configured items, MLAG peer switch state, port count and health-check statistics.

extremeMlagPortLocalPortIfIndex.name: extremeMlagPortLocalPortIfIndex
extremeMlagPortLocalPortIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the local member port of the MLAG port. The specified port ifIndex may be a single port or the master port of a load share port but should not be a load share member port.

extremeMlagPortId.name: extremeMlagPortId
extremeMlagPortId.description: The identifier which is used to identify the MLAG port

extremeMlagPortPeer.name: extremeMlagPortPeer
extremeMlagPortPeer.description: This object identifies the MLAG peer switch with which this port is associated

extremeMlagPortLocalLinkStatus.name: extremeMlagPortLocalLinkStatus
extremeMlagPortLocalLinkStatus.description: Local MLAG Port Status, that can be Active/Disabled/Ready/Port not present. It reflects the status of entire LAG when LAG is used in conjunction with MLAG.

extremeMlagPortRemoteLinkStatus.name: extremeMlagPortRemoteLinkStatus
extremeMlagPortRemoteLinkStatus.description: Remote MLAG Port Status, which can be Up(1) - One or more links are active on the remote switch or Down(2)- No links are active on the remote switch or N/A(3) - The peer has not communicated link state for this MLAG group. It reflects the status of entire LAG when LAG is used in conjunction with MLAG.

extremeMlagPortLocalFailures.name: extremeMlagPortLocalFailures
extremeMlagPortLocalFailures.description: Gives the number of ports that are down in the local MLAG port.

extremeMlagPortRemoteFailures.name: extremeMlagPortRemoteFailures
extremeMlagPortRemoteFailures.description: Gives number of ports that are down in the remote MLAG port

extremeMlagConvergenceControl.name: extremeMlagConvergenceControl
extremeMlagConvergenceControl.description: This object specifies if an ACL can be used on an MLAG port to achieve faster convergence. If an ACL is used, better convergence times can be achieved irrespective of the number of FDB entries present on the MLAG port. The second time can be chosen when convergence time is not an issue and ACLs are to be preserved.

extremeMlagPeerUp.name: extremeMlagPeerUp
extremeMlagPeerUp.description: This trap is sent when the MLAG peer comes up.

extremeMlagPeerDown.name: extremeMlagPeerDown
extremeMlagPeerDown.description: This notification is sent when health check messages are not received from the peer MLAG switch for 3 times the configured hello interval.
